  <section class="compensation-stream" id="questions"><div class="shell">
    <article class="pathway" id="big-picture" data-depth="big"><header><p>BIG PICTURE <b>30 SECONDS</b></p><h2>Compensation is a formula—not a headline.</h2></header>
      <div class="formula-poster" role="img" aria-label="Compensation equals guarantee plus productivity plus quality plus call or leadership minus unseen conditions"><div class="formula-title">COMPENSATION =</div><div class="formula-terms"><span>GUARANTEE</span><b>+</b><span>PRODUCTIVITY</span><b>+</b><span>QUALITY</span><b>+</b><span>CALL / LEADERSHIP</span><b>−</b><span class="condition">UNSEEN CONDITIONS</span></div><div class="formula-caption">The stated salary is only one input.</div></div>
      <div class="three-questions"><p>1. What production threshold must you clear?</p><p>2. What is the conversion factor above it?</p><p>3. What work is actually attributed to you?</p></div>
      <p class="action-callout"><strong>Immediate action:</strong> Ask for the complete written compensation formula and your last two reconciliation statements.</p><p class="pathway-close">The headline salary is only one number. The next two minutes show whether the formula works in your favor.</p><div class="share-controls" data-share-controls><p>Send this to a physician who should see it before their next compensation discussion.</p><button type="button" data-share="copy">Copy link</button><button type="button" data-share="native">Share</button><a data-share="linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url={{@site.url}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a><a data-share="email" href="mailto:?subject=Compensation%20formula&amp;body={{@site.url}}">Email</a></div><a class="text-cta" href="#brief-overview" data-depth-link="brief">Continue to Brief Overview →</a><div class="feedback" data-feedback="big"></div>
    </article>

    <article class="pathway" id="brief-overview" data-depth="brief"><header><p>BRIEF OVERVIEW <b>2 MINUTES</b></p><h2>Compare the economics—not merely the offer.</h2></header>
      <div class="formula-detail"><span>Guarantee</span><b>+</b><span>(Attributed production − threshold) × factor</span><b>+</b><span>quality / call terms</span><b>±</b><span>reconciliation</span></div>
      <div class="offer-compare"><section><p class="offer-label">OFFER A</p><strong>$250,000</strong><span>4,500-unit threshold · $45 factor</span><div class="offer-bar"><i style="width:64%"></i></div></section><section><p class="offer-label">OFFER B</p><strong>$250,000</strong><span>5,500-unit threshold · $45 factor</span><div class="offer-bar"><i style="width:79%"></i></div></section><aside><b>Same headline.</b><p>At 6,000 attributed units, Offer A has 1,500 qualifying units; Offer B has 500. Defined quality, attribution, and reconciliation terms can change the result further.</p></aside></div>
      <div class="explain-grid"><div><b>Threshold</b><p>The point after which the agreement says variable payment begins.</p></div><div><b>Conversion factor</b><p>The stated amount paid for each qualifying production unit.</p></div><div><b>Attribution rules</b><p>The rules that decide which work, collections, or units count as yours.</p></div><div><b>Quality & reconciliation</b><p>Defined adjustments and the process for correcting estimates against actual results.</p></div></div>
      <ol class="question-checklist"><li>What measure is used, and how is it attributed?</li><li>What are the threshold, factor, and payment schedule?</li><li>When and how is the calculation reconciled?</li></ol><section class="decision-tree" aria-label="Compensation decision tree"><b>Decision tree</b><p>Is the measure and attribution written? <strong>No → request it before comparing offers.</strong> <strong>Yes →</strong> model the threshold, factor, quality terms, and reconciliation.</p></section><p class="pathway-close">You can now compare the economics—not merely the offer.</p><a class="text-cta" href="#deep-dive" data-depth-link="deep">Continue to Deep Dive →</a><div class="feedback" data-feedback="brief"></div>
    </article>

    <article class="pathway" id="deep-dive" data-depth="deep"><header><p>DEEP DIVE <b>5 MINUTES</b></p><h2>Build the questions for your next conversation.</h2></header><div class="deep-grid"><section><h3>Worked example <small>Educational</small></h3><p>With a $250,000 guarantee, 6,000 attributed units, a 5,000-unit threshold, and a $45 factor: $250,000 + (6,000 − 5,000) × $45 = <b>$295,000</b>, before any defined adjustments.</p><h3>Negotiation sequence</h3><ol><li>Request definitions and two reconciliation statements.</li><li>Model conservative and expected production.</li><li>Ask what supports each assumption.</li><li>Have qualified counsel review the agreement.</li></ol><h3>Common traps</h3><p>Comparing only salary; accepting undefined attribution; overlooking timing; or relying on this educational example as advice.</p></section><section class="calculator"><h3>Illustrative calculator</h3><label>Guarantee <input data-calc="base" type="number" value="250000" min="0"></label><label>Attributed units <input data-calc="units" type="number" value="6000" min="0"></label><label>Threshold <input data-calc="threshold" type="number" value="5000" min="0"></label><label>Conversion factor <input data-calc="factor" type="number" value="45" min="0" step="0.01"></label><output data-calculator-result aria-live="polite">Illustrative total: $295,000</output><small>Excludes adjustments, benefits, taxes, and agreement-specific definitions.</small></section></div>
      <section class="contract-language"><h3>Sample contract language <small>Educational only</small></h3><blockquote>“The agreement should state the production measure, attribution method, threshold, conversion factor, payment timing, and reconciliation process.”</blockquote></section><section class="checklist-editor"><h3>Action checklist</h3><label><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Request the complete written formula.</label><label><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Identify threshold and conversion factor.</label><label><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Ask about attribution and reconciliation.</label><label><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Seek qualified advice before signing.</label><button type="button" class="download-checklist" data-download-checklist>Download checklist</button></section><section class="knowledge-check"><h3>Knowledge check</h3><p>Which combination makes a productivity payment easiest to evaluate?</p><button type="button" data-check="no">A headline conversion factor alone</button><button type="button" data-check="yes">Measure, attribution, threshold, factor, timing, and reconciliation</button><button type="button" data-check="no">A verbal estimate</button><p data-check-result aria-live="polite"></p></section><p class="pathway-close">You are better prepared for your next compensation discussion than you were five minutes ago.</p><div class="feedback" data-feedback="deep"></div><div class="share-controls" data-share-controls><p>Send this to a physician who should see it before their next compensation discussion.</p><button type="button" data-share="copy">Copy link</button><button type="button" data-share="native">Share</button><a data-share="linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url={{@site.url}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a><a data-share="email" href="mailto:?subject=Compensation%20formula&amp;body={{@site.url}}">Email</a></div><section class="return-loop"><h3>Get the next physician decision question free</h3><p>One useful decision at a time. No spam; unsubscribe anytime.</p><button type="button" class="decision-button" data-portal="signup" data-portal-trigger>Join Free</button><p><b>What physicians focused on this week</b><br>Editorial decision guidance will appear here until real aggregate data is available.</p></section>
    </article>
